Boil @water{350%ml} (exactly) in a #pot{} with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Pour the @Basmati Rice{1} into the pot, turn the heat to its lowest setting and put a #lid{} on top. Leave the rice on low heat for ~{10%minutes}, then rest off the heat for ~{10%minutes}.

> Do not lift the lid until 20 mins are up or the rice won't cook.

Peel and chop the @onion{1} in half lengthways. Slice the onion very thinly into half moons. Peel and very finely dice the @garlic clove{1}. Chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into 2cm cubes.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-low heat. Add the onions with @salt{1/4%tsp} and gently cook for ~{8%minutes}. For the last 2 mins add the @Bang Curry Spice{1} and the garlic.

Turn the heat to medium. Add the @lamb mince{250%g} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and cook until it has browned off. Add @water{1/4%cup}, the @peas{1/2%cup} and tomatoes, place a lid on the pan and cook on low for ~{6%minutes}.

Tip in the cooked rice and stir everything together.

Finally stir through @mint{3%tbsp}(chopped) and @coriander{2%tbsp}(chopped). Serve with a big dollop of @natural yoghurt{1%large dollop}(Greek style) on top.

> Keep adding more fresh herbs if you want - the more the merrier!